{
  "stem": "22869.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they did it with such a rough manner that some of the guys developed some pus and-- and-- and it erased the number.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they had to re-tattoo them, later on, either on the chest or on the number-- or on the hand.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So mine did not develop any problems, so I'm tattooed on my chest up until today, yet.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "How many people, do you think, were tattooed on their chest, altogether?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was the only transport.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think they did away with it right after that because they knew they had problems.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we were 1,500 at that time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "With many of them I kept in touch for quite awhile, in-- while I was in Birkenau and Auschwitz, that had this number.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But by today, I don't think that there are more than five people alive that have a tattooed number on their chest.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And if you want me to name the five, I couldn't.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I couldn't.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "37014.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After I was tattooed, then they took us to the barracks.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they assigned us a bunk and a place.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the next morning, right away, there was a job assignment.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And it took a few days.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I started going out to work.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And somehow I started looking around.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Maybe my brothers are in the same place.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Of course, as I mentioned before, I lost contact with them when they were taken away from home.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And, sure enough, you find faces that you still recognize, which was really hard, because Birkenau was-- was, I would say, almost one of the lowest grades of they way they-- they kept the people there.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And-- and sure enough, I found some people that tell me that they saw my brothers there.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
